We enjoyed our first visit with the restaurant but on our second visit we actually used a Groupon and was actually charged an 18% gratuity charge along with a service charge and on top of that we tipped the server because our initial signature copy did not have the 18% gratuity calculated in your total. After all of the fees, the value of the Groupon is reduced even though you pay one price thinking you're getting what was listed.  And you do not get 2 entrees up to $42.00 value; it's $10 per person and you pay the difference of each meal at the end.  We didn't discover the overcharge until we checked our bank account the next day.  We called to speak with a manager and Henrietta came on the line stating she was a manager but was unable to assist with any adjustments.  She continued to repeat how the 18% is charged because people tend not to tip most times.  We totally understand that but we tipped and was still charged 3 different fees.  She said the manager on duty the day of our visit which apparently was a ghost manager would call us back but we never got a call.  She also said we could come in person to see if the other manager would give us a refund but it would have to be in cash and not on our card.  We asked that the card that we used be credited she said no because most likely we wouldn't get a refund and that we would have to speak with the other manager in person.  Poor customer service and an inconvenience to the customer.
